A nice, big...

09:54.722 --> 09:55.787
GORDON: What the hell is this?

09:55.789 --> 09:56.988
Everyone freeze.

09:56.990 --> 09:57.956
Don't make eye contact.

09:57.958 --> 09:59.558
Eventually he'll go away.

09:59.560 --> 10:01.226
You're using me on the poster?

10:01.228 --> 10:03.195
I'm the face of book-burning?

10:03.197 --> 10:04.863
We didn't have the money to
license a real monster, so...

10:04.865 --> 10:07.432
Oh, is that how you see me... a monster?

10:07.434 --> 10:09.201
Well, if the giant orthopedic shoe fits...

10:09.203 --> 10:10.135
It's not funny, Simon.

10:10.137 --> 10:11.503
- Okay.
- If I'm the bad guy,

10:11.505 --> 10:13.038
it's because you need me to be one.

10:13.040 --> 10:16.308
It serves your pathological
need to be a hero.

10:16.310 --> 10:17.676
You're reducing a very
complex web of neuroses...

10:17.678 --> 10:19.911
Then let me untangle it for you.

10:19.988 --> 10:21.154
Your pro bono crap has

10:21.156 --> 10:23.223
nothing to do with saving the library.

10:23.225 --> 10:25.258
It's all about making sure
that everyone loves you.

10:25.340 --> 10:27.507
And who gives a damn what happens to me?

10:27.509 --> 10:30.810
I'm just Ursula the Sea
Witch to your Little Mermaid.

10:30.812 --> 10:32.946
- Oh, come on, Gordon, I didn't mean...
- Talk to the tentacle.

10:36.350 --> 10:37.550
Gordon, wait.

10:37.552 --> 10:38.518
What?

10:38.520 --> 10:39.919
Oh, I was just doing that thing

10:39.921 --> 10:41.487
where you call out to someone
as they're storming off,

10:41.489 --> 10:42.989
but they don't usually turn around.

10:42.991 --> 10:45.391
I see.

10:46.126 --> 10:47.327
(whispering): No, wait.

10:47.329 --> 10:49.083
SIMON: He's right, it was a bad idea.

10:49.865 --> 10:52.273
- Uh, boss, you know that this already went out, right?
- It did?

10:52.279 --> 10:54.446
- Yeah, hundreds of them.
- Oh, no, no, no, we got to take 'em all down.

10:54.448 --> 10:57.082
- It's too late.
- We... we'll just tell Gordon we took 'em down.

10:57.084 --> 10:58.750
I mean, the election's in two days.

10:58.752 --> 10:59.818
- Oh.
- Yeah, it's just

10:59.820 --> 11:02.153
a little grassroots
campaign in a small town.

11:02.155 --> 11:03.154
(All) Yeah.

11:03.156 --> 11:04.956
Yeah. Yeah. Naperville.

11:04.958 --> 11:08.560
If you check your calendar, it's 2014,

11:08.562 --> 11:10.695
but you sure wouldn't know
it in Naperville, Illinois,

11:10.817 --> 11:12.650
where a group opposed to a tax hike

11:12.652 --> 11:17.455
to save a local library is
organizing a book-burning party

11:17.457 --> 11:21.592
apparently spearheaded by
this unidentified mystery man.

11:21.594 --> 11:22.527
What is wrong with this guy?

11:22.529 --> 11:24.962
What kind of monster burns books?

11:24.964 --> 11:26.297
Around the world, people are asking:

11:26.299 --> 11:29.967
"Who is this madman
and how do we stop him?"

11:29.969 --> 11:31.969
Maybe Gordon doesn't watch the news.

11:31.971 --> 11:33.638
What the hell did you do to me?

11:33.640 --> 11:35.907
And now maybe he's just running
lines for a play he's in?

11:35.909 --> 11:37.708
I'm a pariah out there.

11:37.775 --> 11:39.475
I got egged on the street.

11:39.477 --> 11:41.911
An old lady flicked
her lit cigarette at me.

11:41.913 --> 11:46.749
My latte had a middle
finger drawn in the foam.

11:46.751 --> 11:48.417
Gordon, we are so sorry.
I mean, we never thought

11:48.419 --> 11:49.852
- that this was...
- I don't want to hear it!

11:49.854 --> 11:51.554
I'm blowing your cover.

11:51.556 --> 11:53.389
- No.
- I'm sending out a press release.

11:53.391 --> 11:56.592
Can someone tell me how to
send out a press release?

11:56.594 --> 11:59.428
Or, or we wait till after
the library's been saved.

11:59.430 --> 12:01.030
You'll end up looking like a hero, Gordon.

12:01.182 --> 12:02.214
That was my plan all along.

12:02.216 --> 12:04.483
N... n... n... n... no,
don't play me, Simon.

12:04.485 --> 12:06.051
I'm not playing you, Gordon, you know.

12:06.053 --> 12:08.220
I know right now things look
dire, but a couple of days

12:08.222 --> 12:09.321
from now when we all gather together

12:09.323 --> 12:10.556
for the mock book-burning

12:10.558 --> 12:11.990
and the crowd's there,
ready to lynch you...

12:11.992 --> 12:13.625
- Still looking pretty dire.
- ... we're going to announce

12:13.627 --> 12:15.494
we're not burning the books,
we're saving the library,

12:15.496 --> 12:16.462
and it's all because of you.

12:16.464 --> 12:18.230
You're the man behind it all.

12:18.232 --> 12:19.431
Everyone's going to be cheering for you.

12:19.433 --> 12:20.999
And you'll be the hero this time.

12:21.001 --> 12:23.435
ALL (chanting): Hero, hero...

12:23.437 --> 12:25.204
You just have to have a
little patience, my darling.

12:25.206 --> 12:28.740
Okay, listen, I know you're
pulling this out of your ass.

12:28.742 --> 12:32.911
- No.
- But I do like the idea of being a hero for once.

12:32.913 --> 12:33.912
Yeah.

12:33.914 --> 12:36.114
But what do I do in the meantime?

12:36.116 --> 12:37.549
Hide.

12:37.551 --> 12:39.985
ALL (softly): Hide, hide, hide...

12:39.987 --> 12:42.188
Good luck.

12:42.190 --> 12:44.056
- I'm gonna hide.
- Yeah.

12:44.058 --> 12:45.324
(chanting quietly): hide, hide...

12:48.595 --> 12:51.730
Wow. Just magnificent.

12:51.732 --> 12:54.500
I'm really glad we could all
finally spend some time together.

12:54.502 --> 12:57.036
Oh, yeah. Didn't want to miss this.

12:57.038 --> 12:58.370
Man, look at that spear.

12:58.372 --> 12:59.471
Can you imagine being

12:59.473 --> 13:01.440
- on the business end of that?
- Ooh.

13:01.442 --> 13:03.575
You don't want to miss it for anything.

13:03.577 --> 13:05.010
ZACH: Hey, great tops!

13:05.012 --> 13:07.579
Right on. Book power!

13:07.581 --> 13:09.181
Hey, where's Aaaaandrew... ?

13:09.183 --> 13:10.849
Really? That's a thing?
We're doing that now?

13:10.851 --> 13:13.318
I think they went to go
look at the wall of swords.

13:13.320 --> 13:15.921
Ooh, Zach, do you like swordplay?

13:15.923 --> 13:17.823
Uh, yeah, I'm a guy.

13:17.825 --> 13:19.057
(coughing)

13:19.059 --> 13:20.759
Thank you for bringing me to the museum.

13:20.761 --> 13:23.328
You know me... when it comes
to treating my lady right,

13:23.330 --> 13:25.097
spare no suggested donation.

13:25.099 --> 13:26.331
(chuckles)

13:29.869 --> 13:30.936
Are you okay?

13:30.938 --> 13:33.772
Me? I'm fine.

13:33.774 --> 13:35.140
Yeah, I mean, I'm... I'm here with Dylan.

13:35.142 --> 13:36.908
Of course I am. Why wouldn't I be fine?

13:36.910 --> 13:38.844
Right. You have Dylan.

13:38.846 --> 13:40.779
(men grunting)

13:46.719 --> 13:49.488
(sighs) Lauren, um,

13:49.490 --> 13:50.822
if I tell you something,

13:50.824 --> 13:52.224
you promise you won't tell anyone?

13:52.226 --> 13:53.959
Yeah, of course.

13:53.961 --> 13:55.961
Dylan is...

13:55.963 --> 13:57.762
gay.

13:57.764 --> 13:58.697
What?!

13:58.699 --> 14:00.298
(quieter): What are you saying?

14:00.300 --> 14:01.499
That's crazy.

14:01.501 --> 14:04.035
What? Is everything I knew fake?

14:04.037 --> 14:06.104
Is everything I thought was real

14:06.106 --> 14:08.473
really not real at all?

14:08.475 --> 14:09.574
- You knew?
- I did.

14:09.576 --> 14:11.242
When did you figure it out?

14:11.244 --> 14:13.044
After our fourth date.

14:13.046 --> 14:15.280
When he made me watch a
Raven-Symoné retrospective

14:15.282 --> 14:17.449
and... and he braided my hair.

14:17.451 --> 14:18.817
Oh, the universal tell.

14:18.819 --> 14:19.918
Does everyone know?

14:19.920 --> 14:21.586
DYLAN (in baby talk): Is him wrestled out?

14:21.588 --> 14:22.921
Is him hungry?

14:22.923 --> 14:24.255
Does him want food?

14:24.257 --> 14:25.457
Uh, him... him is hungry.

14:25.459 --> 14:27.625
Him... him... him... him could eat.

14:27.627 --> 14:29.527
Uh... (laughs)

14:29.529 --> 14:30.862
Not everyone.

14:30.864 --> 14:32.530
I mean, Andrew and I figured it out.

14:32.532 --> 14:33.665
He wanted to tell you,

14:33.667 --> 14:35.433
but we didn't want you to feel embarrassed.

14:35.435 --> 14:37.168
Well, that's why I kept it up,

14:37.170 --> 14:38.369
because I felt like an idiot,

14:38.371 --> 14:39.604
and didn't want everyone finding out

14:39.606 --> 14:41.239
and then thinking that I was an idiot.

14:41.241 --> 14:42.707
Which, apparently, they already do.

14:42.709 --> 14:44.342
Are you sure you didn't keep dating him

14:44.344 --> 14:45.309
to make Andrew jealous?

14:45.311 --> 14:46.310
I mean, maybe a little?

14:46.312 --> 14:47.945
No.

14:47.947 --> 14:50.014
I'm... I'm happy that Andrew's happy.

14:50.016 --> 14:51.082
And that he's in love.

14:51.084 --> 14:53.251
And that I get to watch

14:53.253 --> 14:55.720
love bloom every day,
right outside my office.

14:55.722 --> 14:58.456
Oh, good! I thought you'd be bummed.

14:58.458 --> 15:00.725
ZACH: A whole weekend? Just you and me

15:00.727 --> 15:02.393
at your parents' lake house? (laughs): Man!

15:02.395 --> 15:03.961
Andrew is gonna be jealous.

15:03.963 --> 15:05.830
You talk about Andrew a lot.

15:05.832 --> 15:06.831
Did you guys used to date?

15:06.833 --> 15:08.232
(laughing): Date?

15:08.234 --> 15:11.302
No, man, we're just
friends, like you and me.

15:15.374 --> 15:18.209
Oh.

15:18.211 --> 15:21.212
Uh-huh.

15:21.214 --> 15:23.180
O... kay.

15:23.182 --> 15:24.548
Ah!

15:24.550 --> 15:26.450
Uh, him... him... him was not aware.

15:26.452 --> 15:28.085
Him needs a little...

15:28.087 --> 15:29.720
just a little time.

15:34.458 --> 15:36.625
In a few minutes, the
polls are gonna close.

15:36.627 --> 15:37.726
But if we've done our jobs,

15:37.728 --> 15:40.295
these library doors are gonna stay open

15:40.297 --> 15:43.532
because this community said
no to the death of imagination!

15:43.534 --> 15:44.733
ZACH: When the book burners saw us

15:44.735 --> 15:47.169
coming, they ran away

15:47.171 --> 15:48.437
from the power of knowledge!

15:48.439 --> 15:50.539
They were so scared,

15:50.541 --> 15:53.809
they left without their props!

15:53.811 --> 15:55.777
Not even the evil giant
who started this whole thing

15:55.779 --> 15:57.746
had the guts to show his face!

15:57.748 --> 15:59.114
Can I get a whoop-whoop?

15:59.116 --> 16:00.849
(all whooping)

16:00.851 --> 16:01.883
Hey, hey! What's happening?

16:01.885 --> 16:03.785
I thought you were gonna
make me the hero here.

16:03.787 --> 16:05.387
Don't worry... when the vote
is over, I'll bring you out

16:05.389 --> 16:06.955
and reveal that the whole
thing was a campaign to save

16:06.957 --> 16:08.123
the library and you'll reap the glory!

16:08.125 --> 16:09.124
Okay, well hurry up

16:09.126 --> 16:10.692
because my calves are spasming.

16:10.694 --> 16:12.227
- Got it.
- Never should've quit ballet.

16:12.229 --> 16:13.662
Attention, proletariat.

16:13.664 --> 16:15.630
The ballots have been quantified.

16:15.632 --> 16:17.432
And we have emerged

16:17.434 --> 16:20.301
from the hangman's noose unscathed.

16:21.504 --> 16:22.904
Did we win?

16:22.906 --> 16:24.172
That's what I just said.

16:24.174 --> 16:26.040
- We won!
- (all cheering)

16:28.077 --> 16:30.011
You got to make it happen
because I can't feel my legs!

16:30.013 --> 16:31.379
I'm doing it. Everyone?

16:31.381 --> 16:32.981
I have a special surprise.

16:32.983 --> 16:34.983
We would not have won
tonight without the man

16:34.985 --> 16:36.050
I'm about to introduce.

16:36.052 --> 16:38.386
You know him as the face of evil.

16:38.388 --> 16:40.221
- But...
- I can't take it anymore!

16:40.223 --> 16:41.789
- Gordon, Gordon, no... !
- (Gordon muttering)

16:41.791 --> 16:43.324
(crowd gasps, murmurs)

16:43.326 --> 16:45.126
- What are you doing to me?
- MAN: That's him!

16:45.128 --> 16:46.260
- The book hater!
- (all booing)

16:46.262 --> 16:48.062
No, no! No. That isn't who I am.

16:48.064 --> 16:49.097
That's you!

16:49.099 --> 16:50.264
I don't, I don't hate books.

16:50.266 --> 16:52.467
I love books. I'm a reader.

16:52.469 --> 16:53.601
Gordon, Gordon, you're flaming!

16:53.603 --> 16:55.103
I know, it happens when I get nervous.

16:55.105 --> 16:55.903
- No, right there!
- Aah!

16:55.905 --> 16:58.339
Oh! Fire! Bad!

16:58.341 --> 16:59.640
(crowd gasping)

16:59.642 --> 17:00.875
(all scream)

17:00.877 --> 17:02.210
He's burning the books!

17:02.212 --> 17:04.645
No! You're a monster!

17:04.646 --> 17:05.847
Get him!

17:05.848 --> 17:07.781
No, I'm... I'm not a monster!

17:07.784 --> 17:11.085
MAN: Get him! He's a bad man!

17:11.087 --> 17:12.019
He's not bad, he's good!

17:12.021 --> 17:13.287
It's not his fault!

17:13.289 --> 17:14.689
I made him that way!

17:14.691 --> 17:16.958
He's my creation!

17:16.960 --> 17:19.260
Simon, you son of a bitch!

17:19.262 --> 17:20.461
This reminds me of something.

17:20.463 --> 17:22.229
<i>- Twilight?
- Hunger Games?</i>

17:22.231 --> 17:23.564
Seriously?

17:23.566 --> 17:24.734
<i>(cork pops)</i>

17:24.737 --> 17:28.571
"Genius Ad Campaign Revealed."

17:28.574 --> 17:29.974
"Lewis, Roberts & Roberts Saves the Day."

17:29.976 --> 17:32.710
"Homeless Man Arrested for
Masturbating in Library."

17:32.712 --> 17:34.745
See? All is right with the world again.

17:34.747 --> 17:36.981
Whoa, Gordon's on the news.

17:36.983 --> 17:40.251
My thinking was that if we
created a villain character,

17:40.253 --> 17:42.319
that it would change the conversation.

17:42.321 --> 17:45.289
And I volunteered because I care.

17:45.291 --> 17:46.957
Speaking of caring, I'm
sure some of our viewers

17:46.959 --> 17:48.926
want to know how are your injuries

17:48.928 --> 17:50.661
because of the pitchforks?

17:50.663 --> 17:52.363
Numerous and excruciating.

17:52.365 --> 17:55.065
Al... although I was very lucky
that... that church was unlocked,

17:55.067 --> 17:58.268
so I was able to hide
out in the bell tower.

17:58.270 --> 17:59.803
Well, so there we have
it. A nation's villain,

17:59.805 --> 18:02.406
one library's hero.

18:02.408 --> 18:04.241
Uh, Syd? Hey.

18:04.243 --> 18:05.576
I am sorry that Lauren and I didn't

18:05.578 --> 18:07.111
say something sooner about Dylan.

18:07.113 --> 18:08.512
Oh, it's okay.

18:08.514 --> 18:10.214
I mean, the only bummer was that

18:10.216 --> 18:11.315
- I like to hang out with him.
- Ah, sure.

18:11.317 --> 18:12.382
We had a lot in common.

18:12.384 --> 18:13.617
- He's a nice guy.
- Yeah.

18:13.619 --> 18:15.185
Haven't really had that
with anyone in a while.

18:15.187 --> 18:18.088
- Yeah, me neither. (clears throat)
- Except Allie.

18:18.090 --> 18:19.957
Right! No, right, right.

18:19.959 --> 18:22.459
Except Allie, of course,
who's great; she's great.

18:22.461 --> 18:24.328
She's really great. So,
yeah, except for that.

18:24.330 --> 18:25.996
- That's great.
- Okay.

18:27.065 --> 18:28.832
I miss hanging out with you.

18:30.234 --> 18:31.535
You do?

18:31.537 --> 18:34.004
Yeah, I mean, you're, you're a good friend.

18:34.006 --> 18:36.473
I miss you, too... buddy.

18:36.475 --> 18:37.607
(laughs): Okay, cool.

18:37.609 --> 18:38.642
Hey, can I ask you

18:38.644 --> 18:40.610
some really frank sexual advice, actually,

18:40.612 --> 18:41.478
about Allie?

18:41.480 --> 18:42.946
Well, I'm off to grab a beer

18:42.948 --> 18:43.947
with my buddy Dylan.

18:43.949 --> 18:45.282
Wow.

18:45.284 --> 18:47.017
You guys are still hanging out?

18:47.019 --> 18:48.485
Yeah, you know, after we talked

18:48.487 --> 18:50.053
about that kooky misunderstanding,

18:50.055 --> 18:52.355
I realized that D-man is a great guy.

18:52.357 --> 18:54.591
And I'm not just saying
that to make jealous, Andrew.

18:54.593 --> 18:56.259
You and I are totally cool.

18:56.261 --> 18:58.662
I just, I don't know, really
enjoy hanging out with him.

18:58.664 --> 19:00.196
And he's fine that it's platonic?

19:00.198 --> 19:01.231
No, he's totally in love with me.

19:01.233 --> 19:02.465
The Zach bug bit him bad.

19:02.467 --> 19:04.868
But I think I can turn him.

19:06.671 --> 19:08.338
Into a friend.

19:08.340 --> 19:10.573
Well, good luck with that.

19:13.244 --> 19:16.112
Si, I have to say your little
charity stunt worked very well.

19:16.114 --> 19:18.748
We've been getting calls
from new clients all day.

19:18.750 --> 19:20.083
It was all part of my plan.

19:20.085 --> 19:21.251
Oh, please, you had no plan.

19:21.253 --> 19:23.353
You just stumbled upon
a photogenic villain,

19:23.355 --> 19:25.188
and you... you ran with it.

19:25.190 --> 19:26.289
Well, it's your sweaty
Mediterranean features...

19:26.291 --> 19:27.524
they photograph well, my friend.

19:27.526 --> 19:28.825
(laughs) Yeah.

19:28.827 --> 19:30.493
- Touché.
- We make a good team, my man.

19:30.495 --> 19:32.161
- Yeah, we do.
- You're the Beast to my Beauty.

19:32.163 --> 19:34.998
- Oh.
- The Garfunkel to my Simon.

19:35.000 --> 19:37.100
See? That works on two levels
because my name is Simon...

19:37.102 --> 19:38.534
Yeah, yeah, yeah, I get it. Very clever.

19:38.536 --> 19:40.503
- Thank you.
- But no one really ever appreciated Garfunkel.

19:40.505 --> 19:42.196
- Well, Simon did.
- What do you mean? He...

19:42.197 --> 19:43.697
he broke up with him famously.

19:43.742 --> 19:46.109
- For a while they had a nice time.
- Didn't they sue each other?

19:46.111 --> 19:48.044
Don't read too much into it.

19:48.046 --> 19:51.180
My point is this place
wouldn't work without you.

19:51.182 --> 19:53.649
Especially when you hear this.

19:53.651 --> 19:54.784
- What?
- I just took a call

19:54.786 --> 19:56.586
for the biggest buyout offer

19:56.588 --> 19:58.254
we've ever had.

19:58.256 --> 20:01.023
We've had offers before. We
will never sell this company!

20:01.025 --> 20:05.027
Uh, $47 million beg to differ

20:05.029 --> 20:07.029
my Little Brony.

20:07.031 --> 20:09.966
Yes, you are about to
become the proud subsidiary

20:09.968 --> 20:12.702
of Hamasaki Sneakers, Cutlery...

20:12.704 --> 20:15.071
and now... Advertising.

20:15.073 --> 20:16.172
I should've never let
that sympathetic priest

20:16.174 --> 20:17.840
let you out of the bell tower!

20:17.842 --> 20:19.608
We are selling. End of discussion.

20:19.610 --> 20:20.843
No!

20:20.845 --> 20:22.611
What I wouldn't give for
a lit torch right now!

20:22.613 --> 20:23.712
You're a monster!

20:23.714 --> 20:24.980
You made me this way!

20:31.088 --> 20:32.454
No, hefe, tell me this.

20:32.456 --> 20:34.123
(both shouting gibberish)

20:35.959 --> 20:37.226
But now you can see boob...

20:37.228 --> 20:38.827
now you can see all the boobs.

20:38.829 --> 20:40.195
Booby booby boo boo.

20:40.197 --> 20:42.031
No hot chicks. I... I've never seen

20:42.033 --> 20:43.999
seen a girl better than a seven.

20:44.001 --> 20:45.768
Place where old people masturbate.

20:45.770 --> 20:46.969
Oh!

20:46.971 --> 20:49.138
- Whoa!
- Old people masturbate in libraries?

20:49.140 --> 20:51.940
What kind of libraries are
